8 unit(s) Tortilla
260 grams Diced Irish Chicken Breast
2 unit(s) Tomato
50 grams Grated Cheese
1 tin(s) Tomato Paste
1 sachet(s) Sweet Chilli Sauce
2 sachet(s) Mayo
1 unit(s) Bell Pepper
1 unit(s) Cucumber
1 sachet(s) Central American Style Spice Mix
to taste Salt
to taste Pepper
to taste Oil

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.
Halve, deseed and slice the pepper into thin strips.
Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.
Fry the pepper, covered, with a generous pinch of salt for 3-4 mins.
Add the tomato paste and the Central American spice and fry for 1-2 mins more.

Add the chicken to the pan.
Fry until cooked through, 8-10 mins. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don’t worry, this is normal due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

Meanwhile, chop the tomato into 1cm chunks.
Trim the cucumber and quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small chunks.
In a small bowl, combine the sweet chilli sauce with the mayo.
When the chicken is almost done, pop the tortillas into the oven to warm through, 1-2 mins.

Serve chicken, tortillas, tomato, cucumber, sweet chilli mayo and cheese in separate dishes.
Allow everyone to assemble their own tortillas at the table.